Portugal 1997 budget not to boost tax burden . Portugal ' s 1997 budget will not increase the overall weight of tax although there will be some shifting of the burden inside the various tax bands , Secretary of State for the Budget Manuela Arcanjo said . Speaking in a weekend television debate , Arcanjo reaffirmed that the government was basing its budget plans on expected economic growth in 1996 of 2 . 75 - 3 . 25 percent . Inflation was being calculated at 2 . 25 - 2 . 50 percent , while the public sector deficit was targetted at 2 . 9 percent . Private consumption is seen rising 2 . 0 - 2 . 25 percent , while public sector consumption was seen rising under two percent . Exports were seen gaining 9 . 0 - 10 percent , with imports increasing 8 . 0 - 9 . 0 percent . Economic growth should boost employment between 0 . 5 and 1 . 0 percent . - - Lisbon bureau 3511 - 3150035 
